programme.title: Deadly Dinosaurs

programme.title: Planet Dinosaur

programme.title: Horizon

programme.sub-title: The Dinosaur That Fooled the World

programme.desc: David Attenborough learns that descendants of the dinosaur age are alive and well. David explores how they survived the catastrophes that wiped out other species.

programme.title: Science of Walking With Beasts

programme.title: Science of Walking With Beasts
programme.desc: A look at the science that has proved Darwin's idea that intelligent, sophisticated humans have an ancestral connection with the ape.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Ethiopia: Land of Extremes
programme.desc: Landlocked and surrounded by five countries, Ethiopia is one of east Africa's forgotten lands. Seemingly passive deserts in fact seethe with fire, and cloud-piercing peaks shield a secret Eden of canyons and cliff-tops teeming with life.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Virungas: Land of Ice and Fire
programme.desc: It's home to some of the world's most iconic animals  including the African great apes.
programme.sub-title: Virungas: Land of Ice and Fire

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Lake Turkana: Land of the Crocodile

programme.sub-title: Lake Turkana: Land of the Crocodile

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Nile: An African Odyssey
programme.desc: The Nile is the longest river in the world. Ancient Egypt, one of the history's most powerful civilizations, depended hugely upon it. Each year, it flooded, replenishing the fields with fertile silt. This automatic irrigation fueled Egypt's economy.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Okavango: Water in the Desert

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Caribbean: The Wild Side of Paradise

programme.sub-title: Caribbean: The Wild Side of Paradise

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Sri Lanka: Monsoon Island
programme.desc: Lying like a teardrop in the Indian Ocean, Sri Lanka is an island that defies convention. Poised just six degrees above the equator, it's less than 75,000 km sq in size. But it has enough wildlife to rival a continent.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Falkland Islands: Penguin Paradise
programme.desc: The Falkland's bleak, battered, and windswept archipelago lies 460 km from the South American mainland. Rugged mountains and expansive pristine coastline are a unique home for wildlife  especially for one of the world's most iconic flightless birds.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Japan: Islands of Extremes
programme.desc: Japan's 7,000 islands stretch for over 2,400 km, and cover an incredible range of climates. Winter in the central and northern islands can be savage, but summer in the sweltering southern islands couldn't be more different.

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: The Andes: World in the Clouds

programme.sub-title: The Andes: World in the Clouds

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: Venezuela: The Treasure of El Dorado
programme.desc: Venezuela is famous for its lost worlds, its forbidding mountains, huge swamps, and impenetrable jungles, all seemingly cut off in space and time. Yet each is linked, by the mighty river: the Orinoco, the rumoured route to El Dorado, city of gold.
programme.sub-title: Venezuela: The Treasure of El Dorado

programme.desc: Patagonia is a place of extremes  of vast ice fields and snow-capped mountains; of windswept deserts, and violent oceans. Survival here means being tough enough to cope with brutal winters, and canny enough to exploit brief seasons of plenty.
programme.sub-title: Patagonia: The Ends of the Earth

programme.title: World's Greatest: Cruises
programme.desc: There is something seductive about setting sail. Cruises offer us a chance to dip our toes into the 70% of our planet awash with oceans, rivers, and lakes, exploring places that can only be reached by daring to leave the shore.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Iconic Buildings
programme.desc: In construction, only a few buildings can be groundbreaking. Vastly different in shape, size, and function, these diverse buildings prove there is no recipe for greatness, just the fundamental ingredients of vision, bravery, and imagination.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Land Adventures
programme.desc: Most land adventures come with some risk - a chance to confront our deepest fears, resist the pull of the ordinary, and soar into the wild unknown.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Drives
programme.desc: A journey by road expands our horizons, allowing us to explore the depth and breadth of whole countries and continents, stopping whenever and wherever we chose.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Jungle Animals
programme.desc: Encounter gorillas and orangutans, killer tree-dwelling pythons, delightful monkeys, awe-inspiring tigers, and millions of land-dwelling red crabs in Australia, the islands of Southeast Asia, Africa, and the Amazon.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Volcanoes
programme.desc: There are few sights on earth as compelling as a volcanic eruption. Volcanoes have the potential to cause death and widespread destruction in a heartbeat, but they also give rise to new life and ecosystems.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Mega Cities
programme.desc: Mega Cities provide a bustling home to populations of over 10 million. Travel from the high-density living of Shanghai and Bangkok to the sprawling cities of Delhi and Mexico City, each the backdrop for dynamic cultures.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Lost Cities
programme.desc: Once powerful and populous centers of influence, these lost cities are providing clues to how our ancestors existed in the world and remind us that ancient civilizations were not so far removed from our own.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Forest Animals
programme.desc: Forest Animals gets up close with bears, koalas, moose, wolves, weaver ants, and Tasmanian Devils. This episode roves dark forests floors and soars above vast canopies of green in America, China, Laos, and Australia.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Mountains
programme.desc: The earth’s fragile crust has folded and faulted, and nowhere are these natural forces more evident than in the world’s great mountains. Explore the highest peaks of the world’s terrain - the rugged realm between heaven and earth.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Global Cities
programme.desc: Travel to the centers of wealth, power, industry, and innovation. From London to Tokyo, Hong Kong to New York, these are the cities that never sleep. The influence held in these economic hubs unites the global community.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Archipelagos
programme.desc: The romantic notion of island life has always attracted us. Explore the histories, cultures, and unique ways of life on the World’s Greatest Archipelagos - clusters of islands that share common bonds of geography, geology, and genealogy.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Extreme Animals
programme.desc: Extreme Animals features environments hostile to humans, but havens to many animals. Witness gorgeous glow-worms, high flying condors, parched thorny devils, emperor penguins, and polar bears in this journey through life on the edge.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Marine Animals
programme.desc: From the surprises of colorful reef characters to effervescent penguins, killer sharks, and regal whales, dive into the places where nature reveals itself in some of its most marvelous and bizarre forms.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Sacred Sites
programme.desc: Ancient in architecture and detailed in design, these man-made masterpieces stand as testaments to the strength of human faith. These sites endure as a timeless reminder of resilience, respect, and the need to reflect.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Ancient Cities
programme.desc: In Ancient Cities, we journey to these ancestors of influence such as Luang Prabang, Vienna, and Istanbul where religious and cultural centers have shaped the ways in which we view the world around us and continue to do so in modern times.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Capital Cities
programme.desc: With visionaries, politicians, and activists, these metropolises are defined as the official seats of government. Dublin, Washington, and Taipei share broad avenues, museums, and monuments, but are as varied as the countries they represent.

programme.title: War Story: Bomb Girls Remember
programme.desc: During the Second World War, 250,000 Canadian women helped to build the arsenal of democracy. These young women met the challenges of factory work and helped to win the Second World War, and by doing so, paved the way for future generations.

programme.title: War Story: Bomber Command: Getting Home
programme.desc: In this film, Bomber Command personnel and a Luftwaffe pilot take the viewer through the frightening reality of fighting in the skies as they try to get a damaged bomber home.

programme.title: War Story: Bomber Command: Hitting Back
programme.desc: After surviving the German bombing campaign of British cities, RAF Bomber Command struck back against Germany. The devastating consequences of raids, for both for the young men in the skies and the people on the ground, are portrayed in this film.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Japan continues its suicidal resistance, and invading it looks costly. After 2 atomic bombs, the Emperor intervenes and stops the War. Stalin grabs territory in East Asia. The War is over, and the Atomic Era and the Cold War start.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: In 1945, Germany is crumbly on both fronts. The Western Allies cross the Rhine and take most of Germany, while the Red Army quickly advances into Berlin. After Hitler's suicide, Germany surrenders and is divided among the allied powers.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: The Marines succeed in the "island hopping" strategy against suicidal resistance. The US Navy establishes supremacy, cutting off Japan.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: The Western Allies secure supply routes that will allow them to enter Germany, and the Ardennes counter-offensive fails. The Red Army advances rapidly. The SS implements the Holocaust.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: After a careful campaign of disinformation that throws the German defenders off-guard, the Western Allies finally land on Normandy.France is liberated.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Their attack on the Soviet Union having failed, the German Army suffers a series of counter-offensives on the Eastern Front. Wehrmacht's losses are huge as the Soviets advance West.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Allies turn the tide in the Atlantic, where initially German U-Boats harass freely convoys to supply Britain. The route to bring American soldiers who will land on D-Day is clear.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Italy's failed attacks in the Mediterranean region draw in the Germans.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour

programme.title: Kathleen Shannon On Film Feminism Other Dreams
programme.desc: With intelligence and humour, documentary filmmaker, Kathleen Shannon speaks her formative years at the National Film Board, and the gradual awakening of an unshakeable determination to give women filmmakers a chance to tell their stories of the world

programme.title: Chaque Enfant
programme.desc: This is the story of a baby who appears mysteriously on the doorstep of a busy executive, and who is subsequently bounced from household to household down the block. Nobody in the community is interested in caring for the baby without a name.

programme.title: Horse Drawn Magic
programme.desc: The Caravan Stage Company is the only horse-drawn open-air theatre in the world. Every summer it tours British Columbia and Alberta, bringing live entertainment to communities where television is often the main diversion.

programme.title: The Impossible Takes A Little Longer
programme.desc: Documents the work and personal lives of five physically disabled women. It shows how they are coping with the problems they share with all women, the problems they share with other disabled women and those unique to their particular circumstances.

programme.title: Holy Angels
programme.desc: Jay Cardinal Villeneuve’s short documentary Holy Angels powerfully recaptures Canada’s colonialist history through impressionistic images and the fragmented language of a child.

programme.title: Julie Obrien
programme.desc: This film is loosely structured around Julie O'Brien, eleven’s school assignment to write an essay about the old times in Newfoundland, how they have changed, how they are still remembered.

programme.title: Twenty Years Of Feminist Filmmaking
programme.desc: A clip montage for presentation at the National Action Committee on the Status of Women to commemorate the 20th anniversary of Studio D and the National Action Committee.

programme.title: Waiting
programme.desc: The patient Dinkas of South Sudan endure famine amid civil strife. Aid arrives in Alek, but distribution is delayed to prevent unrest, revealing the stark reality of hunger.

programme.title: Children Of War
programme.desc: A remarkable documentary in which teenagers from war-torn countries, filmed in interaction with Canadian high-school students, speak with dignity, maturity and candor about the struggles of their people and the suffering they have endured.

programme.title: Safe Distance, A
programme.desc: A Safe Distance examines the services needed by and available to battered women. The film looks at some innovative approaches to providing services and accommodation for battered women in rural, northern, and Native communities.

programme.title: Le Grand Serpent Du Monde
programme.desc: A young forty-something, Tom Paradise refuses to grow up. Behind the wheel of his bus he drives endlessly through the city, tracing out the path of his life, dreaming of the landscape of the American West that forever impressed him

programme.title: Koromousso Big Sister
programme.desc: This film challenges cultural taboos surrounding female sexuality and explores the fight to take back ownership of bodies and to overcome the trauma of female genital mutilation.

programme.title: The Man Who Stole Dreams
programme.desc: This enchanting and magical animation film, an ode to our dreams during the night, celebrates the creative imagination, uniqueness, and the human spirit. The plot involves a man who steals the dreams of villagers, the tries to sell them back to the them.

programme.title: The Way It Is
programme.desc: The Way It Is" explores divorce's effects on a family, centered on twelve-year-old Helen. Her journey to acceptance offers insights for all ages, suitable for family-life courses, single-parent groups, and counseling.

programme.title: Turnaround A Story Of Recovery
programme.desc: Turnaround: A Story of Recovery" follows five women battling addiction at Aurora House. This documentary offers insight for families, friends, and professionals interested in alternative treatment methods.

programme.title: Mother Earth/La Terre Notre Mere
programme.desc: Mother Earth is a short, evocative, poetic film that celebrates life on our planet. This documentary film looks at the reality of human beings; the earth is our home and we are profoundly connected to all other beings.

programme.title: Royal Journey
programme.desc: A documentary account of the five-week visit of Princess Elizabeth and the Duke of Edinburgh to Canada and the United States in the fall of 1951.

programme.title: Goddess Remembered
programme.desc: This poetic documentary is a salute to 35 000 years of "pre-history," to the values of ancestors only recently remembered, and to the goddess-worshipping religions of the ancient past.

programme.title: Ladies And Gentlemen Mr Leonard Cohen
programme.desc: Produced in 1965, this is an informal portrait of the Montreal poet, novelist and songwriter, Leonard Cohen. He is seen reading his poetry to a rapt audience and also alone, or relaxing with family and friends.

programme.title: Physics Of Sorrow, The
programme.desc: The Physics of Sorrow tracks an unknown man’s life as he sifts through memories of his youth in Bulgaria through to his increasingly rootless and melancholic adulthood in Canada.

programme.title: The Town Mouse And The Country Mouse
programme.desc: Evelyn Lambart's animation style shines in this short film adapting an Aesop fable. It contrasts two mice's lifestyles, advocating for simplicity and peace over luxury amid danger.

programme.title: Writer In The Nuclear Age A Conversation With Margaret Laurence
programme.desc: Margaret Laurence tackles peace-related issues in this short film: writer's social responsibility, language's impact, nuclear threat, and more. Ideal for sparking discussions across various subjects.

programme.title: Waiting For Fidel
programme.desc: Three Canadians, including ex-premier Joseph Smallwood and NFB director Michael Rubbo, travel to Cuba, aiming to cast Fidel Castro. Their journey offers insights into Cuba's changes and their own views.

programme.title: Ryan
programme.desc: Ryan is based on the life of Ryan Larkin, a Canadian animator who, 30 years ago, produced some of the most influential animated films of his time.

programme.title: Its Just Better
programme.desc: At the farmhouse on Cape Breton Island where Shawn Peter Dwyer, age ten, lives with his mother and nine brothers and sisters, a team effort keeps the family functioning.

programme.title: Men of the Deeps
programme.desc: Men of the Deeps is a moving portrait of a group of former Cape Breton miners gathered together by their love of song. They are all members of the Men of the Deeps chorus, whose performances of traditional and contemporary songs evoke their working lives

programme.title: Freddy Quinn LIVE - Lieder, die das Leben schrieb: Teil 1
programme.desc: Er reiste um die Welt, begeisterte ein Millionenpublikum und schaffte es zehn Mal auf Platz 1 der deutschen Charts. Freddy Quinn ist einer der letzten großen Entertainer Deutschlands. 2002 gab der Österreicher ein bewegendes Abschieds-Konzert in Wien.

programme.title: Andreas Fulterer - Mein Weg
programme.desc: Andreas Fulterer ist seiner Heimat Südtirol immer treu geblieben. Im Musikspecial "Mein Weg" zeigt er uns die schönsten Plätze und ist zudem mit seinen größten Hits in Konzertausschnitten zu sehen. Ein wunderschöner, besinnlicher Musikfilm.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast im Brandnertal
programme.desc: In dieser Ausgabe von "Lieder, Land & Leute" entführt Sängerin und Moderatorin Dagmar Obernosterer die Zuschauer in das wunderschöne Brandnertal. Vor der alpinen Kulisse des Vorarlberg geben Stars aus Schlager und Volsmusik ihre Lieder zum Besten.

programme.title: Gala der Stars auf hoher See
programme.desc: GoldStar TV sendet von der 'Costa Classica'. Frederic Meisner und Jutta Niedhardt stellen Ihnen das Traumschiff vor. Für musikalische Unterhaltung ist selbstverständlich auch gesorgt. Freuen Sie sich auf Stars wie Roland Kaiser, WIND, André Stade u.v.a

programme.title: Goldies: Folge 3
programme.desc: So schön kann doch kein Mann sein / Hell wie ein Diamant / Oh wann kommst du / Arizona Man / Ich bin verliebt in die Liebe / Die Sonne und du

programme.title: Stars auf hoher See: Unterwegs im Mittelmeer
programme.desc: Schlager Ahoi! GoldStar TV sticht auf der imposanten MSC Magnifica in See. Matthias Reim, Claudia Jung, Anita und Alexandra Hofmann, Andrea Rischka, René Ulbrich und viele mehr präsentieren ihren größten Hits.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast in Gamlitz an der Südsteirischen Weinstraße
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer besucht die Region rund um Gamlitz an der südsteirischen Weinstraße. Sie begrüßt Oswald Sattler, die Stoakogler, Gilbert u.v.a. Auch Harmonikaweltmeister Primosch Zvir gibt eine Kostprobe seines Könnens.
programme.sub-title: zu Gast in Gamlitz an der Südsteirischen Weinstraße

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast in der Steiermark
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer präsentiert diesmal in der Steiermark große Stars der volkstümlichen Schlagermusik: Die Mooskirchner, Die Schäfer, Die Aufgeiger, Reiner Kirsten, Die Jauntaler, Eva-Maria, Die Krieglacher und Die Neffen.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: Winter aus Sterzing
programme.desc: Unsere musikalische Reise führt uns nach Sterzing in Südtirol. Moderatorin Dagmar Obernosterer begrüßt in dem malerischen Ort Interpreten wie Die jungen Zillertaler, Bergfeuer und Oswald Sattler.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast in Bad Kleinkirchheim
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer präsentiert Bad Kleinkirchheim und die Region Nockberge in Kärnten. Sie besucht die Nockalmstrasse mit dem Naturbegegnungspark Silva Magica, den Millstätter See und die Kaiserburg, Hausberg von Ski-Olympiasieger Franz Klammer.

programme.title: O Desejo de Charlie
programme.desc: Um veterano militar volta para casa depois de um afastamento por estresse pós-traumático. Com seu novo cachorro, ele descobre em pleno Natal um novo propósito em sua vida - auxiliar ex-militares que precisam de ajuda.

programme.title: O milagre de natal Jonathan Toomey
programme.desc: Quando um menino perde o presépio de madeira que o liga ao pai morto, sua mãe preocupada convence um entalhador solitário e mal-humorado a criar um substituto e permitir que seu filho o veja trabalhar nele.

programme.title: Só Pode Ser Amor
programme.desc: Durante a temporada de Natal, três irmãs terão que decidir o que fazer com sua vida romântica quando partem para encontrar a família para as festas e seus respectivos pares surgem na cidade para tentar uma segunda chance.

programme.title: Aventuras do K-9: Uma História de Natal
programme.desc: Kassie, suas amigas e seu cachorro, Scoot, organizam um evento de arrecadação de fundos de férias, mas precisam proteger o dinheiro de alguns bandidos para salvar o Natal.

programme.title: Um Anjo em Minha Vida
programme.desc: Uma jovem adolescente rica e mimada está prestes a descobrir que o verdadeiro valor não está nas etiquetas de preços e "coisas", mas nos atos gentis de ajudar os outros, tudo com a mão amiga de um anjo da guarda.

programme.title: Desejo de Natal
programme.desc: Sem dinheiro e abandonada pelo marido com três filhos, Martha não está tendo o melhor fim de ano da sua vida. Mas ela muda de cidade e redescobre a esperança quando encontra um emprego e uma rede de apoio em uma pacata lanchonete de interior.

programme.title: Natal Feliz
programme.desc: Após a morte de seu pai, um menino cria um vínculo especial com o cachorro de um vizinho e aprende a ser um homem ajudando seus avós durante uma tempestade de inverno.

programme.title: Sobrevivendo Às Festas com Parentes
programme.desc: As irmãs Miranda e Lyla se reúnem para o Natal com suas famílias. Ao longo de três dias, alegria e caos causam estragos nos planos de férias das famílias e as antigas rivalidades entre irmãos surgem para sabotar a esperança diversão de fim de ano.

programme.title: Um Natal Encantado
programme.desc: Hugo, de doze anos, ainda acredita em elfos, mas é provocado por seus colegas, então decide se forçar a crescer. Mas quando sua família sai de férias de Natal, ele descobre que elfos moram no hotel.

programme.title: O Desejo de Charlie
programme.desc: Um veterano militar volta para casa depois de um afastamento por estresse pós-traumático. Com seu novo cachorro, ele descobre em pleno Natal um novo propósito em sua vida - auxiliar ex-militares que precisam de ajuda.

programme.desc: Crie uma atmosfera calorosa de férias em sua casa com as imagens e sons do Natal, filmados em alta definição.

programme.desc: Cozy up to the special edition fireplace, just in time for the Holidays. The soft crackling of burning wood will turn your home into a calming retreat.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: It's a Christmas Thing
programme.desc: Cuando Megan, de nueve años, dedica su deseo navideño a ayudar a su madre Cara a encontrar el amor, su carta termina volviéndose viral. ¿Cara seguirá el consejo de su hija y encontrará el amor?

programme.title: Christmas Chalet, The
programme.desc: Una amante de la Navidad y divorciada reserva un viaje a un chalet con su madre y su hija. Sin embargo, el mismo chalet está reservado para un único escritor que odia la Navidad. Juntos aprenden la magia de la Navidad y la familia.

programme.title: A Song for Christmas
programme.desc: Charlotte es nueva en la ciudad y se da la circunstancia de que su madre ha intimado con el padre de la que parece que se va a convertir en su peor enemiga.

programme.title: 12 Regalos de navidad
programme.desc: Cuando Anna, una pintora desempleada, no puede llegar a fin de mes, la contratan para convertirse en la compradora navideña personal de Marc, un ejecutivo corporativo tenso.

programme.title: Una navidad real
programme.desc: Una ejecutiva de publicidad muy trabajadora, se enamora de un consultor que es un príncipe disfrazado.

programme.title: La mejor Navidad
programme.desc: Gloria, enfocada en su trabajo en Miami después de su divorcio, envía a sus hijos a pasar la Navidad con su exmarido en Jalisco. Lo que no imaginan es que esta decisión les va a cambiar la vida.

programme.title: The Santa Squad
programme.desc: Allie, una profesora de arte desempleada, acepta un trabajo para ayudar a un viudo rico y a sus dos hijas. Mientras Allie levanta el espíritu navideño de la familia con adornos navideños, su amabilidad se ve recompensada con un regalo inesperado: ¡Amor!

programme.title: Ghosts of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Un adivino le dice a una mujer con un problema de "fantasmas" en serie en aplicaciones de citas que debe resolver su pasado y hacer las paces con todos aquellos a quienes engañó antes de Navidad o estará destinada a nunca encontrar el amor verdadero.

programme.title: Una Navidad muy Britanica
programme.desc: El vuelo de la cantante de ópera Jessica a su concierto en Viena se retrasa y ella se queda varada en Yorkshire. El único lugar para quedarse es un bed and breakfast en un pueblo encantador dirigido por un apuesto viudo llamado Andrew.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: It's a Christmas Thing
programme.desc: Cuando Megan, de nueve años, dedica su deseo navideño a ayudar a su madre Cara a encontrar el amor, su carta termina volviéndose viral. ¿Cara seguirá el consejo de su hija y encontrará el amor?

programme.title: Christmas Chalet, The
programme.desc: Una amante de la Navidad y divorciada reserva un viaje a un chalet con su madre y su hija. Sin embargo, el mismo chalet está reservado para un único escritor que odia la Navidad. Juntos aprenden la magia de la Navidad y la familia.

programme.title: A Song for Christmas
programme.desc: Charlotte es nueva en la ciudad y se da la circunstancia de que su madre ha intimado con el padre de la que parece que se va a convertir en su peor enemiga.

programme.title: 12 Regalos de navidad
programme.desc: Cuando Anna, una pintora desempleada, no puede llegar a fin de mes, la contratan para convertirse en la compradora navideña personal de Marc, un ejecutivo corporativo tenso.

programme.title: Una navidad real
programme.desc: Una ejecutiva de publicidad muy trabajadora, se enamora de un consultor que es un príncipe disfrazado.

programme.title: La mejor Navidad
programme.desc: Gloria, enfocada en su trabajo en Miami después de su divorcio, envía a sus hijos a pasar la Navidad con su exmarido en Jalisco. Lo que no imaginan es que esta decisión les va a cambiar la vida.

programme.title: The Santa Squad
programme.desc: Allie, una profesora de arte desempleada, acepta un trabajo para ayudar a un viudo rico y a sus dos hijas. Mientras Allie levanta el espíritu navideño de la familia con adornos navideños, su amabilidad se ve recompensada con un regalo inesperado: ¡Amor!

programme.title: Ghosts of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Un adivino le dice a una mujer con un problema de "fantasmas" en serie en aplicaciones de citas que debe resolver su pasado y hacer las paces con todos aquellos a quienes engañó antes de Navidad o estará destinada a nunca encontrar el amor verdadero.

programme.title: Una Navidad muy Britanica
programme.desc: El vuelo de la cantante de ópera Jessica a su concierto en Viena se retrasa y ella se queda varada en Yorkshire. El único lugar para quedarse es un bed and breakfast en un pueblo encantador dirigido por un apuesto viudo llamado Andrew.

programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: It's a Christmas Thing
programme.desc: Cuando Megan, de nueve años, dedica su deseo navideño a ayudar a su madre Cara a encontrar el amor, su carta termina volviéndose viral. ¿Cara seguirá el consejo de su hija y encontrará el amor?

programme.title: Christmas Chalet, The
programme.desc: Una amante de la Navidad y divorciada reserva un viaje a un chalet con su madre y su hija. Sin embargo, el mismo chalet está reservado para un único escritor que odia la Navidad. Juntos aprenden la magia de la Navidad y la familia.

programme.title: A Song for Christmas
programme.desc: Charlotte es nueva en la ciudad y se da la circunstancia de que su madre ha intimado con el padre de la que parece que se va a convertir en su peor enemiga.

programme.title: 12 Regalos de navidad
programme.desc: Cuando Anna, una pintora desempleada, no puede llegar a fin de mes, la contratan para convertirse en la compradora navideña personal de Marc, un ejecutivo corporativo tenso.

programme.title: Una navidad real
programme.desc: Una ejecutiva de publicidad muy trabajadora, se enamora de un consultor que es un príncipe disfrazado.

programme.title: La mejor Navidad
programme.desc: Gloria, enfocada en su trabajo en Miami después de su divorcio, envía a sus hijos a pasar la Navidad con su exmarido en Jalisco. Lo que no imaginan es que esta decisión les va a cambiar la vida.

programme.title: The Santa Squad
programme.desc: Allie, una profesora de arte desempleada, acepta un trabajo para ayudar a un viudo rico y a sus dos hijas. Mientras Allie levanta el espíritu navideño de la familia con adornos navideños, su amabilidad se ve recompensada con un regalo inesperado: ¡Amor!

programme.title: Ghosts of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Un adivino le dice a una mujer con un problema de "fantasmas" en serie en aplicaciones de citas que debe resolver su pasado y hacer las paces con todos aquellos a quienes engañó antes de Navidad o estará destinada a nunca encontrar el amor verdadero.

programme.title: Una Navidad muy Britanica
programme.desc: El vuelo de la cantante de ópera Jessica a su concierto en Viena se retrasa y ella se queda varada en Yorkshire. El único lugar para quedarse es un bed and breakfast en un pueblo encantador dirigido por un apuesto viudo llamado Andrew.

programme.title: DIE HALBINSEL
programme.desc: Berge sind für die gesamte Morphologie Iberiens verantwortlich. Sie sind auch der Geburtsort der Flüsse, die das Leben im gesamten Gebiet verteilen. Hier gibt es viele Wälder, jeder mit seinem eigenen Ökosystem. Iberische Gebirgsketten haben unterschiedliche Gesichter und Persönlichkeiten, ebenso wie ihre wilden Bewohner.

programme.title: Wilde Überlebenskünstler
programme.desc: Die Formen der Fortpflanzung in der Natur sind sehr unterschiedlich, und nicht immer gehört Sex dazu. Grundsätzlich werben die Männchen um die Weibchen, die den stärksten oder schönsten Kandidaten wählen, den mit den meisten Vorzügen oder, wenn sie Glück haben, den besten Vater.

programme.title: Naturparadiese in Lateinamerika: Patagonien
programme.desc: Diese Serie feiert Lateinamerikas dramatischste Regionen, von den Hohen Anden zum dampfenden Amazonas, von den windigen Steppen Patagoniens zu den Sümpfen Venezuelas – atemberaubende Schönheit und eine aufregende, vielfältige Tierwelt.

programme.title: Kanadas Küstenwölfe
programme.desc: Der Great Bear Regenwald an der Westküste Kanadas ist die Heimat der Küstenwölfe. Sie haben felsige Riffe, bewaldete Inseln und die tobende Pazifikküste zu ihrer Heimat gemacht. Das besondere an ihnen ist, dass sie nicht nur an Land jagen, sondern auch im Ozean. Die Dokumentation begleitet Naturführer Cal Humchitt und sein Team auf den Spuren der Küstenwölfe.

programme.title: Wilde Schönheiten: Ägypten
programme.desc: Ägypten bedeutet Pharaonen, Pyramiden und vor allem – Wüste. In der feindlichen Umgebung leben alle Arten von Tieren. Die alten Ägypter glaubten, dass diese Kreaturen die Natur, Mond, Tag und Nacht kontrollieren.

programme.title: Mitten im Südafrika
programme.desc: Das Meer verwandelt sich zusehends. Die azurblaue See von Durban unterscheidet sich grundlegend von der rauen Meeresküste des Kaps. Gemeinsam mit dem österreichischen Haiforscher Dietmar Posch startet Andreas auf eine Expedition in die warmen Gewässer vor der Küste

programme.title: DIE HALBINSEL
programme.desc: Berge sind für die gesamte Morphologie Iberiens verantwortlich. Sie sind auch der Geburtsort der Flüsse, die das Leben im gesamten Gebiet verteilen. Hier gibt es viele Wälder, jeder mit seinem eigenen Ökosystem. Iberische Gebirgsketten haben unterschiedliche Gesichter und Persönlichkeiten, ebenso wie ihre wilden Bewohner.

programme.title: Der Neuseeland-Aal
programme.desc: Der Extremangler Jeremy Wade reist nach Papua-Neuguinea.

programme.desc: Der Extremangler Jeremy Wade begibt sich auf die Reise zum Großen Afrikanischen Grabenbruch.

programme.desc: Unsichtbare Angreifer lauern in den abgelegenen Bergen und Dschungeln von Fidschi.

programme.title: Der afrikanische Tigersalmler
programme.desc: Das Verschwinden von drei Männern in Russland wird für Jeremy Wade zu einem rätselhaften Fall.

programme.title: Der nordamerikanische Musky
programme.desc: Die Jagd nach einem 6 Meter großen Seemonster, das Menschen in der kanadischen Wildnis angreift.

programme.title: Die Rückkehr zum afrikanischen Tigersalmler
programme.desc: Jeremy Wade begibt sich auf die Suche nach dem grausamen und fleischfressenden Tigerfisch.

programme.title: Der Arapaima
programme.desc: Die Legende besagt, dass in den Tiefen des Amazonas ein großer böser Fisch lebt.

programme.title: Der südamerikanische Zitteraal
programme.desc: Jeremy Wade begibt sich in den Dschungel von Südamerika, um einen gefährlichen Fisch aufzuspüren.

programme.title: Nach dem Wasser
programme.desc: Ein Erdbeben vor Sumatra löste 2004 den Tsunami aus. Der Film schildert die Umstände in der Region Aceh und wie die SOS-Kinderdörfer es schafften, Nothilfe zu leisten und bis heute mit ihren Programmen Kindern und Erwachsenen zu helfen.

programme.title: Kenia
programme.desc: Asha und Stephen sind im SOS-Kinderdorf in Nairobi aufgewachsen und haben das Beste daraus gemacht. Sie sind "The next Generation". Die Generation, die es schaffen will und auch schaffen wird.

programme.title: Waschbären, unsere neuen Nachbarn?
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Ursprünglich stammen Waschbären aus Nordamerika. Inzwischen breiten sie sich auch in Europa aus. Da sie 2016 von der EU als invasiv, also als Gefahr für das Ökosystem eingestuft wurden, werden sie massiv bejagt. Die Berliner Tierärztin Dr. Mathilde Laininger engagiert sich für ein friedliches Miteinander zwischen Mensch und Waschbär.

programme.title: Leben mit dem Tod
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Auf der indonesischen Insel Sulawesi dreht sich schon zu Lebzeiten der Bewohner alles die Beerdigung. Der Totenkult der Toraja kann viel Geld verschlingen, was die Bestattung verstorbener Verwandter oft auf Jahre unmöglich macht. So behalten die Angehörigen ihre Toten so lange im Haus, bis sie das Geld für die aufwendigen Feierlichkeiten haben.

programme.title: Pelota, die baskische Leidenschaft
programme.desc: Kaum eine Sportart verbindet die Menschen im Baskenland so sehr wie Pelota. Die Region im Grenzgebiet von Frankreich und Spanien, sieht sich als eigenständige Provinz mit einer gemeinsamen Kultur, Sprache und Identität. Das Pelota-Spiel, bei dem ein Ball per Hand oder Schläger gegen eine Hauswand geworfen wird, ist wichtiger Teil davon.

programme.title: Sardiniens wertvolle Muschelseide
programme.desc: Planet Wetlweit: Jedes Frühjahr findet auf Sardinien eine Prozession zu Ehren des Heiligen Antiochus statt. Die Einwohner legen Kostüme an, in den Kirchen werden Altartücher ausgelegt, die noch mit Muschelseide verziert sind - jenen Fasern, die die Fischer seit Jahrhunderten dem Meer entnahmen. Inzwischen sind diese Muscheln streng geschützt

programme.title: Cordóba, die Stadt der Patios
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Der ganze Stolz von Córdoba sind die Patios der Stadt - begrünte Innenhöfe, deren Wurzeln bis in die römische Antike und die Zeit der maurischen Herrschaft in Andalusien zurückreichen. Einmal im Jahr findet ein traditioneller Wettbewerb statt. Dann dreht sich alles um die Frage: Wer hat den schönsten Patio der ganzen Stadt?

programme.title: Kourou: Palmen, Raketen, Gefängnisinseln
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Lange war Französisch-Guayana an der Küste Südamerikas ein Schreckensort für Gefangene. Die Zuchthäuser dort galten als die härtesten Frankreichs. Heute sind von ihnen nur noch Ruinen übrig, die restauriert werden. Frankreich beginnt, dieses dunkle Kapitel seiner Geschichte aufzuarbeiten, nur einige Kilometer entfernt vom Weltraumbahnhof Kourou.

programme.title: Flügel, Schnabel, Superhirn
programme.desc: Jahrzehnte lang glaubten wir Menschen, Vögel wären schlichte Gemüter und hauptsächlich von ihren Instinkten geleitet. Erst vor relativ kurzer Zeit mussten wir entdecken, wie falsch diese Annahme war. Während der Dreharbeiten für diesen Film, der von Terra Mater Factual Studios und Parthenon Entertainment hergestellt wurde, besuchten die Regisseure John Capener und Steve Nicholls Forscherautoritäten des Konrad Lorenz- und des Max Planck-Instituts und der Universitäten Wien, Oxford, Cambridge und Straßburg und stießen auf erstaunliche Intelligenzleistungen.

Sie sind Beuteltiere, teils sehr kleine, ihr weiches Fell trägt mal Punkte, mal Streifen. Doch sie alle haben etwas Entscheidendes gemeinsam: ihren Appetit auf Fleisch, Blut und die Lust zu jagen!

programme.title: Buddy Rich, Tom Warrington, Bob Kaye & John Marshall
programme.sub-title: Buddy Rich Big Band - The North Sea Jazz
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. Buddy Rich, one of the most influential jazz drummers of all time, performed at the North Sea Jazz Festival of 1978 with his orchestra. Rich's drumming was known for its remarkable speed and dexterity, which he achieved without any formal education.

programme.title: Astrud Gilberto, Marcelo Gilberto, David Sacks & Gil Goldstein
programme.sub-title: Astrud Gilberto Band Live at Estival Lugano 1985
programme.desc: Since 1977, Estival is a summer jazz festival in Switzerland, Lugano. Estival offers a thrilling and particularly surprising line-up that explores the rich world of contemporary music whilst promoting the understanding of different cultures, tolerance, and co-existence. “The Girl From Ipanema”, Astrud Gilberto's second name. The Brazilian bossa-nova and samba singer gives an outstanding, swinging performance at Estival Lugano. The band features Marcello Gilberto, David Sacks, Gil Goldstein, and Eduardo da Fonseca. Astrud started to record her own compositions in the '70s. She has recorded songs in Portuguese, English, Spanish, Italian, French, German, and Japanese.

programme.title: Christian Scott
programme.desc: In 2019, the vibrant city of Sofia, Bulgaria, hosted the International A to JazZ Festival. Among the featured acts was the trailblazing jazz trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah. This genre-defying artist captivated the audience with his eclectic “stretch music” an approach that incorporates hip-hop and reaches back through the American canon into African percussion and its rich melodic content. Trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah's quintet, which includes drummer Corey Fonville, percussionist Weedie Braimah, pianist Lawrence Fields, and bass guitarist Max Mucha, delivered a performance that defied boundaries and expectations.

programme.title: La Velle
programme.sub-title: Rhoda Scott & La Velle: Hammond, Soul and Blues
programme.desc: American soul and jazz organist Rhoda Scott spent most of her career in France, where she earned recognition far greater than that accorded to her in the United States. There was never any doubt about what instrument she would play as a child. "It's really the most beautiful instrument in the world,” she once stated in an interview. “The first thing I did was take my shoes off and work the pedals.” This performance at the French Festival Jazz à Vienne is extra special. Not only because of the beautiful location, but also because she shares the stage with American gospel and blues singer La Velle. Together they give an intimate and beautiful show in the antique theatre of Vienne.

programme.title: Anita Oday
programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: Miles Davis
programme.desc: American trumpeter Miles Davis (1926-1991) was a pioneering jazz musician from the late 1940s to the late 1980s. His influence on 20th century music is hard to overstate, as he trailblazed bebop, cool jazz, hardbop, modal jazz, and electronic music. On October 11, 1964, Miles Davis performed at Teatro Dell'Arte in Milan. With tenor saxophonist Wayne Shorter, pianist Herbie Hancock, bassist Ron Carter and drummer Tony Williams, Davis performed Autumn Leaves, My Funny Valentine, All Blues, All of You, and Joshua.

programme.title: George Shearing & Neil Swanson
programme.sub-title: George Shearing Duo feat. Neil Swainson
programme.desc: British pianist George Shearing enjoyed an international reputation as an instrumentalist, arranger, and composer. Equally at home on the classical concert stage as in jazz clubs, he was recognized for his inventive, orchestrated jazz. In this live recording from the Munich Philharmonie, Shearing played in a duo format with Canadian double bassist Neil Swainson. The repertoire consisted of a selection of compositions by Shearing himself, among them ‘Lullaby Of Birdland', which is a standard in jazz repertoire.

programme.title: Kenny G
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. In 1987, smooth jazz saxophonist and crowd-favorite Kenny G serenaded those attending the North Sea Jazz Festival in The Hague. After beginning his career in the Love Unlimited Orchestra, he now brings his own band for this hypnotic performance.

programme.sub-title: The Reunion Tour: Live at Wembley
programme.desc: Filmed at Wembley Arena, London, this concert film will give all fans a spectacular Live experience from start to finish. Classic Duran Duran featuring unforgettable version of their hits: "Rio", "Hungry Like The Wolf", "The Reflex" and many more…

programme.title: Eurythmics
programme.desc: Annie Lennox and Dave Stewart came from very different backgrounds, but both pursued a career in music from an early age. Annie Lennox and Dave Stewart were two wildly different characters. She was a tenement girl from Aberdeen, who'd managed to claw her way out of what was obviously quite a hard upbringing, He was the kind of Wearside Durham Jack the Lad who was something of a musical prodigy. Annie studied the flute at the Royal Academy of Music but had to work as a waitress to get by. It was at her workplace that she was introduced to Dave Stewart through a mutual friend. They would soon form their first band, The Tourists The Tourists disbanded after legal issues between Pete Coombes and the label. It freed Annie and Dave, who wanted to expand their creativity further. Together they formed the Eurythmics and released their debut album, In the Garden. In the Garden achieved little commercial success and the duo chose to retreat to a small home studio in London's Chalk Farm, where they were free to develop a new sound They began to work with synthesisers, a choice that would lead them to their breakthrough hit, Sweet Dreams Are Made Of This. The success of the single led to a re-release of Love is a Stranger. The band, now big on both sides of the Atlantic, had another hit on their hands. The band quickly worked on their follow-up album, Touch. It would become their first number one in the UK and produced a succession of hit singles. Touch also saw them experiment with even more musical styles Featuring archive material, music videos Who's That Girl, Sweet Dreams (Are Made Of This) and, exclusive insights from music critics and journalists Michael Bonner (Uncut Magazine), Hamish MacBain (Shortlist), John Aizlewood (Evening Standard) Rock Legends Eurythmics tells the story of one of Britain's enduring rock bands.

programme.title: Bryan Ferry
programme.desc: Bryan Ferry was born into a northern working-class family as the Second World War came to a close. His father handled pit ponies for the surrounding coal mines. Whilst studying fine art at Newcastle University, Ferry became exposed to the R&B, jazz and soul records that came in via the city's shipping ports. Ferry moved to London's Notting Hill at the start of the 1970s. It was here that he would quickly form his band, Roxy Music. He had such a strong vision for the band that before signing to Island Records he had the band's debut album and artwork completed. The first single, Virginia Plain was so remarkable in its maturity it entered the UK charts at number four .

programme.title: Allman Brothers
programme.desc: The Allman Brothers Band combined deeply Southern strains of music — blues, country, and gospel — with boisterous rock & roll and their jazzy, jam-oriented style. Thus they created the "New South" sound, drafting a template to be used for decades by everyone from Lynyrd Skynyrd and the Marshall Tucker Band to My Morning Jacket and the Drive-By Truckers.

programme.title: Rod Stewart
programme.desc: Roderick David Stewart was born in Highgate North London as the Second World war was coming to a close. His neighbourhood was bombed just 30 minutes before his birth, giving him the feeling that he almost didn't make it into the world. One of Rod's earliest exposures to music was with the family gatherings around the piano in which they would sing songs by the 30s baritone singer, Al Jolson. The young Rod was also caught up in the wake of Rock and Roll music that swept 50s Britain. Rod developed a love of Otis Redding and Sam Cooke and took to the Blues circuit with his first band The Dimensions. However Rod lost vocal duties to Jimmy Powell and soon left the group but fate intervened in the form of singer Long John Baldry. Baldry brought Stewart into his band The Hoochie Coochie Men, but like many of Rod's musical projects in the mid 60s it was short lived. However Baldry and Stewart were soon back together as part of Steam Packet along with Julie Driscoll. Rod had embraced the Mod look by this stage and the nickname Rod the Mod began to stick as his recognition grew. After leaving Steam Packet Rod was quickly picked up by former Yard Birds guitarist Jeff Beck. Rod had been a fan of The Yard Birds and this opportunity not only gave him a chance to sing with a hero, but also tour extensively across the US in the late 60s. Whilst on tour with Jeff Beck, Rod met guitarist Ronnie Wood, the two remained friends and when the Jeff Beck group disbanded, Rod and Ronnie became part of a new band that would be key to the success of both of their careers, Faces Despite his success with Faces, Rod released his own debut solo album An Old Raincoat Won't Ever Let You Down. The bulk of which was recorded during his time in the Jeff Beck group Things would change dramatically for Stewart as a solo artist with the release of his third solo album 1971's Every Picture Tells A Story. The album would make him the first solo artist to achieve the number 1 position in both the US and the UK. And would give him his first smash hit single Maggie May Featuring archive material, music videos “Maggie May” “In The Morning” and, exclusive insights from music critics and journalists Michael Bonner (Uncut Magazine), Hamish MacBain (Shortlist), John Aizlewood (Evening Standard) Rock Legends Rod Stewart tells the story of one of Britain's enduring rock stars.

programme.title: Quatuor Ebène
programme.sub-title: Beethoven - String Quartet No. 7 & 13, and Op. 133
programme.desc: Renowned French string quartet Quatuor Ébène marked the 250th birth anniversary of Ludwig van Beethoven (1770-1827) with a remarkable project: recording all of the great composer's sixteen string quartets. For five years, violinists Pierre Colombet and Gabriel Le Magadure, violist Marie Chilemme, and cellist Raphaël Merlin immersed themselves in Beethoven's 650 pages of sheet music. Their efforts culminated in the performance of the composer's complete repertoire for string quartet, which covers three decades of Beethoven's musical creativity, during six impressive concerts at Philharmonie de Paris in the autumn of 2020. Quatuor Ébène explored every facet of Beethoven's string quartet repertoire: from the youthful Opus 18 string quartets to the Razumovsky, Harp, and Serioso quartets (Opus 59, 74, and 95) from his middle period, and finally, the depth of his late quartets (Opus 127 to 135). This program features Quatuor Ébène performing Beethoven's String Quartet No. 7 in F major, Op. 59, No. 1, known as “Razumovsky” String Quartet No. 13 in B-flat major, Op. 130 and the monumental Great Fugue, Op. 133. This concert performance was recorded at Philharmonie de Paris on October 12, 2020.

programme.title: Julie Berthollet, Camille Berthollet, Guillaume Vincent & Ensemble Appassionato
programme.sub-title: Berthollet Sisters at Théâtre des Champs-Élysées
programme.desc: For this exceptional recital, recorded in 2019 at the Théâtre des Champs-Élysées, Camille (cello) and Julie Berthollet (violin) are accompanied by pianist Guillaume Vincent and the Ensemble Appassionato under the direction of Mathieu Herzog. The two musical sisters have chosen a repertoire which crosses genres and eras to explore the expressive palette of the violin and cello, from the baroque of Vivaldi to the jazzy notes of Django Reinhardt and Stéphane Grapelli. Among the works on the program are Brahms Hungarian Dances No. 5 and No. 6, Karl Jenkins' Palladio, 'Theme from Forrest Gump' by Alan Silvestri, Schumann's Piano Quintet, Op. 44, The Red Violin by Corigliano, Hungarian Rhapsody, op. 68 by Popper, Minor Swing by Reinhardt/Grappeli and Csárdás by Monti.

programme.title: Elena Bashkirova, Baiba Skride, Itamar Zorman & Krzysztof Chorzelski
programme.desc: During late summer every year, some of the world's best musicians meet in Israel for the Jerusalem International Chamber Music Festival (JCMF), established by pianist Elena Bashkirova and Yeheskell Beinisch. In 2016, the 19th festival was dedicated to the music of interrelated composers, such as Brahms and Schumann, and Schubert and Beethoven – performed by outstanding artists such as Sir András Schiff, Baiba Skride, Menahem Pressler and Emmanuel Pahud in the halls of the Jerusalem YMCA. This documentary film features excerpts from performances of the following works: Johannes Brahms's String Sextet no. 1, Op. 18 Franz Schubert's Arpeggione Sonata in A minor, D. 821 Antonín Dvořák's Piano Quintet no. 2 in A major, Op. 81 Ferruccio Busoni's Fantasia Contrappuntistica Felix Mendelssohn's Piano Trio no. 1, Op. 49 and Ludwig van Beethoven's Quintet for Piano and Winds, Op. 16.

programme.title: Gewandhausorchester Leipzig, Andris Nelsons & Kristine Opolais
programme.desc: Andris Nelsons, together with his then-wife, the great soprano Kristine Opolais and the Gewandhausorchester Leipzig present a program dedicated to Antonin Dvořák, singing the melodies that the composer hid in all layers of his music with tender, warm, soft colors. Nelsons' tempos remain calm and relaxed, allowing the omnipresent beauty of Dvořák's music to unfold and flood the Gewandhaus. The program opens with Othello, a Concert Overture for Orchestra, Op. 93. Opolais performs “Song to the Moon” from Rusalka, “Songs my Mother Taught Me” from Gypsy Songs, Op. 55/4. This is followed by the Polonaise and 'O, marno, marno to je' from Rusalka and 'Dobrá! Já mu je dám!... Jak je mi?' from Smetana's opera Dalibor. The concert closes with a performance of Dvořák's Symphony no. 9 in E Minor, Op. 95 (“From the New World”). Recorded at the Gewandhaus, Leipzig in May 2017.

programme.title: Kinderstube Wildnis Bei den Elefanten
programme.desc: Pünktlich zur Regenzeit versammeln sich unzählige Dickhäuter im ostafrikanischen Samburu Nationalpark. Wenn es genügend Gräser, Sträucher und Wasserstellen gibt, bekommen die Elefanten ihren Nachwuchs. Auch Maya kommt als erstes Baby einer jungen Elefantenkuh zur Welt. Nach der ersten Portion Milch und einem kühlenden Schlammbad machen sich Mutter und Kind auf den Weg zurück zur Herde. Der Neuzugang wird euphorisch von allen Familien-Mitgliedern begrüßt. Die Freundschaften und Bindungen, die in der Gruppe entstehen, halten bei den Dickhäutern ein Leben lang. Bis zum Beginn der Trockenzeit bleiben Maya ein paar herrliche Wochen nur zum Spielen und krafttanken im sicheren Reservat. Pünktlich zum Aufbruch der Herden am Ende der Regenzeit, müssen die Kleinen stark genug für die erste lange Wanderung sein. Die geplanten Routen sind voller Gefahren: Reißende Flüsse voll lauernder Krokodile, hungrige Löwen und Wilderer außerhalb des Nationalparks werden zur nervenaufreibenden Bewährungsprobe für Maya.

programme.title: Waschbären, unsere neuen Nachbarn?
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Ursprünglich stammen Waschbären aus Nordamerika. Inzwischen breiten sie sich auch in Europa aus. Da sie 2016 von der EU als invasiv, also als Gefahr für das Ökosystem eingestuft wurden, werden sie massiv bejagt. Die Berliner Tierärztin Dr. Mathilde Laininger engagiert sich für ein friedliches Miteinander zwischen Mensch und Waschbär.

programme.title: Leben mit dem Tod
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Auf der indonesischen Insel Sulawesi dreht sich schon zu Lebzeiten der Bewohner alles die Beerdigung. Der Totenkult der Toraja kann viel Geld verschlingen, was die Bestattung verstorbener Verwandter oft auf Jahre unmöglich macht. So behalten die Angehörigen ihre Toten so lange im Haus, bis sie das Geld für die aufwendigen Feierlichkeiten haben.

programme.title: Pelota, die baskische Leidenschaft
programme.desc: Kaum eine Sportart verbindet die Menschen im Baskenland so sehr wie Pelota. Die Region im Grenzgebiet von Frankreich und Spanien, sieht sich als eigenständige Provinz mit einer gemeinsamen Kultur, Sprache und Identität. Das Pelota-Spiel, bei dem ein Ball per Hand oder Schläger gegen eine Hauswand geworfen wird, ist wichtiger Teil davon.

programme.title: Sardiniens wertvolle Muschelseide
programme.desc: Planet Wetlweit: Jedes Frühjahr findet auf Sardinien eine Prozession zu Ehren des Heiligen Antiochus statt. Die Einwohner legen Kostüme an, in den Kirchen werden Altartücher ausgelegt, die noch mit Muschelseide verziert sind - jenen Fasern, die die Fischer seit Jahrhunderten dem Meer entnahmen. Inzwischen sind diese Muscheln streng geschützt

programme.title: Cordóba, die Stadt der Patios
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Der ganze Stolz von Córdoba sind die Patios der Stadt - begrünte Innenhöfe, deren Wurzeln bis in die römische Antike und die Zeit der maurischen Herrschaft in Andalusien zurückreichen. Einmal im Jahr findet ein traditioneller Wettbewerb statt. Dann dreht sich alles um die Frage: Wer hat den schönsten Patio der ganzen Stadt?

programme.title: Kourou: Palmen, Raketen, Gefängnisinseln
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Lange war Französisch-Guayana an der Küste Südamerikas ein Schreckensort für Gefangene. Die Zuchthäuser dort galten als die härtesten Frankreichs. Heute sind von ihnen nur noch Ruinen übrig, die restauriert werden. Frankreich beginnt, dieses dunkle Kapitel seiner Geschichte aufzuarbeiten, nur einige Kilometer entfernt vom Weltraumbahnhof Kourou.

programme.desc: 낙선재는 헌종 대에 지어진 건물로, 사대부 주택의 형식을 따랐으나 궁궐 침전의 양식이 가미되었습니다. 때문에 다른 곳에서는 쉽게 찾아볼 수 없는 다양한 문양의 장식이 있어 조선 후기 건축의 축적된 기량을 엿볼 수 있죠. 일반인 비공개 지역인 창덕궁 낙선재 후원을 바라보며 휴식을 취해보세요. ※ 창덕궁 낙선재 (보물 1764호) / 창덕궁 (1997년 유네스코 세계문화유산)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: [신비롭고 아름다운 비경] 청송 주산지 EP.3
programme.desc: 주산지는 조선 경종(1720년) 10월에 준공하였습니다. 주산지의 맑은 물은 주산현 꼭대기 별바위에서 계곡을 따라 흘러 주산지에 머무르고 주왕산 영봉에서 뻗친 울창한 수림으로 둘러싸여 있으며, 물위에 떠있는 듯한 왕버들과 어우러져 별천지에 온 것 같이 한적하면서도 아늑한 분위기를 자아냅니다. ※ 청송 주산지 일원 (명승 제 105호) / 청송세계지질공원 (2017년 유네스코 세계지질공원)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 봄을 맞이하다. 궁중병과 봄차림상
programme.desc: 봄과 가장 잘 어울리는 완벽한 간식, 궁중병과를 만드는 소리를 담아봤습니다. 봄향기 가득한 화사한 진달래로 만드는 진달래 화전, 다양한 재료로 예쁘게 색을 낸 삼색쌀강정, 그리고 달콤하고 톡 쏘는 오미자 화채를 만드는 모습을 함께 감상해보시죠. (박영미 / 국가무형문화재 조선왕조궁중음식 이수자)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 칼끝에서 피어나는 장인정신. 소반장
programme.desc: 반(小盤)이란 음식을 담은 그릇을 올려 놓는 작은 상으로, 한국의 식생활에서 부터 제사의례에 이르기까지 여러 용도로 쓰이며, 이것을 만드는 기술 또는 그 장인(匠人)을 소반장이라 합니다. 작지만 부족함이 없으며 실용성과 멋을 두루 갖춘 우리 전통의 소리를 ASMR 풀버젼으로 감상해보시죠. (이종덕 / 국가무형문화재 소반장 전승교육사)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 정성과 인내의 흔적. 명주짜기
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널우리나라는 이미 신라 시대에 견직물을 당나라에 보낼 만큼 그 기술이 뛰어났으며, 명주는 전통 직조과정에서 가장 많이 생산되었던 직물입니다. 뽕나무를 재배하고 누에를 치는 일부터, 실을 뽑고 타래를 만들고, 베틀에서 한 필의 명주를 짜기까지. 전통 길쌈의 고된 노동 속에서 정성과 인내의 흔적을 만나봅시다. (두산손명주연구회 / 국가무형문화재 명주짜기 보유단체)

programme.title: 기품있는 한옥의 멋. 고택의 하루
programme.desc: 해 뜨기 전 너른 마당을 빗자루로 쓰는 소리, 어머니의 밥 짓는 정지의 풍경, 타닥타닥 장작개비가 타들어 가는 아궁이의 소리 등 지친 일상 속에서 하루쯤 푸근하게 쉬어가고 싶은 550년 역사를 자랑하는 오래된 고택에서 다양한 일상의 풍경을 이른 아침부터 밤까지 생생하게 들려드립니다. ※ 안동 진성이씨 온혜파 종택 (국가민속문화재 제295호)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 선비의 길. 낙죽장도
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널장도는 몸에 지니는 자그마한 칼로 일상생활이나 호신용 또는 장신구로 사용되었는데, 이 장도를 만드는 기능과 그 기능을 가진 사람을 장도장이라 합니다. 장도 중에 낙죽장도는 7마디 이상의 대나무에 선비들이 좋아하는 시문이나 무늬를 인두로 새긴 칼로서 일반 은장도와 달리 선비의 칼로 알려졌어요. (한상봉 / 국가무형문화재 장도장 보유자)

programme.title: 바람을 만드는 장인. 선자장
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널선자장은 전통 부채를 만드는 장인입니다. 특히 대나무의 겉대를 합쳐서 만드는 접부채인 합죽선은 현재까지 전승되는 최고 수준의 정교함과 세련미를 갖춘 우리 고유의 부채입니다. 공방에서 들리는 부채만드는 소리에 귀를 귀울여봐요. (김동식 / 국가무형문화재 선자장 보유자)

programme.title: Buddy Rich, Tom Warrington, Bob Kaye & John Marshall
programme.sub-title: Buddy Rich Big Band - The North Sea Jazz
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. Buddy Rich, one of the most influential jazz drummers of all time, performed at the North Sea Jazz Festival of 1978 with his orchestra. Rich's drumming was known for its remarkable speed and dexterity, which he achieved without any formal education.

programme.title: Astrud Gilberto, Marcelo Gilberto, David Sacks & Gil Goldstein
programme.sub-title: Astrud Gilberto Band Live at Estival Lugano 1985
programme.desc: Since 1977, Estival is a summer jazz festival in Switzerland, Lugano. Estival offers a thrilling and particularly surprising line-up that explores the rich world of contemporary music whilst promoting the understanding of different cultures, tolerance, and co-existence. “The Girl From Ipanema”, Astrud Gilberto's second name. The Brazilian bossa-nova and samba singer gives an outstanding, swinging performance at Estival Lugano. The band features Marcello Gilberto, David Sacks, Gil Goldstein, and Eduardo da Fonseca. Astrud started to record her own compositions in the '70s. She has recorded songs in Portuguese, English, Spanish, Italian, French, German, and Japanese.

programme.title: Christian Scott
programme.desc: In 2019, the vibrant city of Sofia, Bulgaria, hosted the International A to JazZ Festival. Among the featured acts was the trailblazing jazz trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah. This genre-defying artist captivated the audience with his eclectic “stretch music” an approach that incorporates hip-hop and reaches back through the American canon into African percussion and its rich melodic content. Trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah's quintet, which includes drummer Corey Fonville, percussionist Weedie Braimah, pianist Lawrence Fields, and bass guitarist Max Mucha, delivered a performance that defied boundaries and expectations.

programme.title: La Velle
programme.sub-title: Rhoda Scott & La Velle: Hammond, Soul and Blues
programme.desc: American soul and jazz organist Rhoda Scott spent most of her career in France, where she earned recognition far greater than that accorded to her in the United States. There was never any doubt about what instrument she would play as a child. "It's really the most beautiful instrument in the world,” she once stated in an interview. “The first thing I did was take my shoes off and work the pedals.” This performance at the French Festival Jazz à Vienne is extra special. Not only because of the beautiful location, but also because she shares the stage with American gospel and blues singer La Velle. Together they give an intimate and beautiful show in the antique theatre of Vienne.

programme.title: Anita Oday
programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: Miles Davis
programme.desc: American trumpeter Miles Davis (1926-1991) was a pioneering jazz musician from the late 1940s to the late 1980s. His influence on 20th century music is hard to overstate, as he trailblazed bebop, cool jazz, hardbop, modal jazz, and electronic music. On October 11, 1964, Miles Davis performed at Teatro Dell'Arte in Milan. With tenor saxophonist Wayne Shorter, pianist Herbie Hancock, bassist Ron Carter and drummer Tony Williams, Davis performed Autumn Leaves, My Funny Valentine, All Blues, All of You, and Joshua.

programme.title: George Shearing & Neil Swanson
programme.sub-title: George Shearing Duo feat. Neil Swainson
programme.desc: British pianist George Shearing enjoyed an international reputation as an instrumentalist, arranger, and composer. Equally at home on the classical concert stage as in jazz clubs, he was recognized for his inventive, orchestrated jazz. In this live recording from the Munich Philharmonie, Shearing played in a duo format with Canadian double bassist Neil Swainson. The repertoire consisted of a selection of compositions by Shearing himself, among them ‘Lullaby Of Birdland', which is a standard in jazz repertoire.

programme.title: Kenny G
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. In 1987, smooth jazz saxophonist and crowd-favorite Kenny G serenaded those attending the North Sea Jazz Festival in The Hague. After beginning his career in the Love Unlimited Orchestra, he now brings his own band for this hypnotic performance.

programme.sub-title: The Reunion Tour: Live at Wembley

programme.title: Eurythmics
programme.desc: Annie Lennox and Dave Stewart came from very different backgrounds, but both pursued a career in music from an early age. Annie Lennox and Dave Stewart were two wildly different characters. She was a tenement girl from Aberdeen, who'd managed to claw her way out of what was obviously quite a hard upbringing, He was the kind of Wearside Durham Jack the Lad who was something of a musical prodigy. Annie studied the flute at the Royal Academy of Music but had to work as a waitress to get by. It was at her workplace that she was introduced to Dave Stewart through a mutual friend. They would soon form their first band, The Tourists The Tourists disbanded after legal issues between Pete Coombes and the label. It freed Annie and Dave, who wanted to expand their creativity further. Together they formed the Eurythmics and released their debut album, In the Garden. In the Garden achieved little commercial success and the duo chose to retreat to a small home studio in London's Chalk Farm, where they were free to develop a new sound They began to work with synthesisers, a choice that would lead them to their breakthrough hit, Sweet Dreams Are Made Of This. The success of the single led to a re-release of Love is a Stranger. The band, now big on both sides of the Atlantic, had another hit on their hands. The band quickly worked on their follow-up album, Touch. It would become their first number one in the UK and produced a succession of hit singles. Touch also saw them experiment with even more musical styles Featuring archive material, music videos Who's That Girl, Sweet Dreams (Are Made Of This) and, exclusive insights from music critics and journalists Michael Bonner (Uncut Magazine), Hamish MacBain (Shortlist), John Aizlewood (Evening Standard) Rock Legends Eurythmics tells the story of one of Britain's enduring rock bands.

programme.title: Bryan Ferry
programme.desc: Bryan Ferry was born into a northern working-class family as the Second World War came to a close. His father handled pit ponies for the surrounding coal mines. Whilst studying fine art at Newcastle University, Ferry became exposed to the R&B, jazz and soul records that came in via the city's shipping ports. Ferry moved to London's Notting Hill at the start of the 1970s. It was here that he would quickly form his band, Roxy Music. He had such a strong vision for the band that before signing to Island Records he had the band's debut album and artwork completed. The first single, Virginia Plain was so remarkable in its maturity it entered the UK charts at number four .

programme.title: Allman Brothers
programme.desc: The Allman Brothers Band combined deeply Southern strains of music — blues, country, and gospel — with boisterous rock & roll and their jazzy, jam-oriented style. Thus they created the "New South" sound, drafting a template to be used for decades by everyone from Lynyrd Skynyrd and the Marshall Tucker Band to My Morning Jacket and the Drive-By Truckers.

programme.title: Rod Stewart
programme.desc: Roderick David Stewart was born in Highgate North London as the Second World war was coming to a close. His neighbourhood was bombed just 30 minutes before his birth, giving him the feeling that he almost didn't make it into the world. One of Rod's earliest exposures to music was with the family gatherings around the piano in which they would sing songs by the 30s baritone singer, Al Jolson. The young Rod was also caught up in the wake of Rock and Roll music that swept 50s Britain. Rod developed a love of Otis Redding and Sam Cooke and took to the Blues circuit with his first band The Dimensions. However Rod lost vocal duties to Jimmy Powell and soon left the group but fate intervened in the form of singer Long John Baldry. Baldry brought Stewart into his band The Hoochie Coochie Men, but like many of Rod's musical projects in the mid 60s it was short lived. However Baldry and Stewart were soon back together as part of Steam Packet along with Julie Driscoll. Rod had embraced the Mod look by this stage and the nickname Rod the Mod began to stick as his recognition grew. After leaving Steam Packet Rod was quickly picked up by former Yard Birds guitarist Jeff Beck. Rod had been a fan of The Yard Birds and this opportunity not only gave him a chance to sing with a hero, but also tour extensively across the US in the late 60s. Whilst on tour with Jeff Beck, Rod met guitarist Ronnie Wood, the two remained friends and when the Jeff Beck group disbanded, Rod and Ronnie became part of a new band that would be key to the success of both of their careers, Faces Despite his success with Faces, Rod released his own debut solo album An Old Raincoat Won't Ever Let You Down. The bulk of which was recorded during his time in the Jeff Beck group Things would change dramatically for Stewart as a solo artist with the release of his third solo album 1971's Every Picture Tells A Story. The album would make him the first solo artist to achieve the number 1 position in both the US and the UK. And would give him his first smash hit single Maggie May Featuring archive material, music videos “Maggie May” “In The Morning” and, exclusive insights from music critics and journalists Michael Bonner (Uncut Magazine), Hamish MacBain (Shortlist), John Aizlewood (Evening Standard) Rock Legends Rod Stewart tells the story of one of Britain's enduring rock stars.

programme.title: Quatuor Ebène
programme.sub-title: Beethoven - String Quartet No. 7 & 13, and Op. 133
programme.desc: Renowned French string quartet Quatuor Ébène marked the 250th birth anniversary of Ludwig van Beethoven (1770-1827) with a remarkable project: recording all of the great composer's sixteen string quartets. For five years, violinists Pierre Colombet and Gabriel Le Magadure, violist Marie Chilemme, and cellist Raphaël Merlin immersed themselves in Beethoven's 650 pages of sheet music. Their efforts culminated in the performance of the composer's complete repertoire for string quartet, which covers three decades of Beethoven's musical creativity, during six impressive concerts at Philharmonie de Paris in the autumn of 2020. Quatuor Ébène explored every facet of Beethoven's string quartet repertoire: from the youthful Opus 18 string quartets to the Razumovsky, Harp, and Serioso quartets (Opus 59, 74, and 95) from his middle period, and finally, the depth of his late quartets (Opus 127 to 135). This program features Quatuor Ébène performing Beethoven's String Quartet No. 7 in F major, Op. 59, No. 1, known as “Razumovsky” String Quartet No. 13 in B-flat major, Op. 130 and the monumental Great Fugue, Op. 133. This concert performance was recorded at Philharmonie de Paris on October 12, 2020.

programme.title: Julie Berthollet, Camille Berthollet, Guillaume Vincent & Ensemble Appassionato
programme.sub-title: Berthollet Sisters at Théâtre des Champs-Élysées
programme.desc: For this exceptional recital, recorded in 2019 at the Théâtre des Champs-Élysées, Camille (cello) and Julie Berthollet (violin) are accompanied by pianist Guillaume Vincent and the Ensemble Appassionato under the direction of Mathieu Herzog. The two musical sisters have chosen a repertoire which crosses genres and eras to explore the expressive palette of the violin and cello, from the baroque of Vivaldi to the jazzy notes of Django Reinhardt and Stéphane Grapelli. Among the works on the program are Brahms Hungarian Dances No. 5 and No. 6, Karl Jenkins' Palladio, 'Theme from Forrest Gump' by Alan Silvestri, Schumann's Piano Quintet, Op. 44, The Red Violin by Corigliano, Hungarian Rhapsody, op. 68 by Popper, Minor Swing by Reinhardt/Grappeli and Csárdás by Monti.

programme.title: Elena Bashkirova, Baiba Skride, Itamar Zorman & Krzysztof Chorzelski
programme.desc: During late summer every year, some of the world's best musicians meet in Israel for the Jerusalem International Chamber Music Festival (JCMF), established by pianist Elena Bashkirova and Yeheskell Beinisch. In 2016, the 19th festival was dedicated to the music of interrelated composers, such as Brahms and Schumann, and Schubert and Beethoven – performed by outstanding artists such as Sir András Schiff, Baiba Skride, Menahem Pressler and Emmanuel Pahud in the halls of the Jerusalem YMCA. This documentary film features excerpts from performances of the following works: Johannes Brahms's String Sextet no. 1, Op. 18 Franz Schubert's Arpeggione Sonata in A minor, D. 821 Antonín Dvořák's Piano Quintet no. 2 in A major, Op. 81 Ferruccio Busoni's Fantasia Contrappuntistica Felix Mendelssohn's Piano Trio no. 1, Op. 49 and Ludwig van Beethoven's Quintet for Piano and Winds, Op. 16.

programme.title: Gewandhausorchester Leipzig, Andris Nelsons & Kristine Opolais
programme.desc: Andris Nelsons, together with his then-wife, the great soprano Kristine Opolais and the Gewandhausorchester Leipzig present a program dedicated to Antonin Dvořák, singing the melodies that the composer hid in all layers of his music with tender, warm, soft colors. Nelsons' tempos remain calm and relaxed, allowing the omnipresent beauty of Dvořák's music to unfold and flood the Gewandhaus. The program opens with Othello, a Concert Overture for Orchestra, Op. 93. Opolais performs “Song to the Moon” from Rusalka, “Songs my Mother Taught Me” from Gypsy Songs, Op. 55/4. This is followed by the Polonaise and 'O, marno, marno to je' from Rusalka and 'Dobrá! Já mu je dám!... Jak je mi?' from Smetana's opera Dalibor. The concert closes with a performance of Dvořák's Symphony no. 9 in E Minor, Op. 95 (“From the New World”). Recorded at the Gewandhaus, Leipzig in May 2017.
